cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Finite-State Transducers in Lean 4"
message: "If you use this software or build on the proofs, please cite it using the metadata below."
type: software
authors:
  - name: "Claude, Opus Models Family"
  - family-names: Alekseev
    given-names: Anton
abstract: >-
  A self-contained, machine-checked development of the core theory of
  finite-state transducers and the rational relations they realize, formalized
  in Lean 4 with no dependency on Mathlib. Includes closure properties, both
  directions of Kleene's theorem, determinization and Myhill-Nerode for DFAs,
  the twinning property, the Choffrut subsequentiality characterization in both
  directions, and an effective (executable) decision criterion for twinning.
  Every result is proved with no sorry and depends only on propext and
  Quot.sound (never Classical.choice).
keywords:
  - Lean 4
  - formal verification
  - finite-state transducers
  - rational relations
  - automata theory
  - Choffrut's theorem
  - twinning property
  - subsequential transducers
license: Beerware
repository-code: "https://github.com/alexeyev/finite-state-transducers-lean"
version: "1.0.0"
date-released: "2026-06-19"
